Some people advocate creating artifacts (packages, tarballs, anything), 
so that you have an authoritative, unchangable source of truth for your deployed application revisions on the contrary to
deploying directly from git branches, which are fungible and can be rewritten or destroyed.


https://www.reddit.com/r/cscareerquestions/comments/e095pv/how_i_got_7_offers_heres_what_i_learned/
